A clinicopathologic study of carcinoma of the papilla of Vater. With a view to clarify the concept of early carcinoma of the papilla Vateri, we examined the records of 26 patients who were treated at the National Cancer Center Hospital in the past 22 years. The following three factors were considered prognostically important for the identification of carcinomas at early stages: Histologically, 1: cancerous infiltration should not reach the proper muscle layer of the duodenum (d-factor) 2: no infiltration into the pancreas should be observed